															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=571081&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227484" alt="qntm" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=571081)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;" >qntm</a></span> <span class="odate time_1583002427 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Feb 2020 18:53</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4524214">
									

<p>Immense thanks to users naepicfail, Rimple and literallymechanical for their editorial feedback on this chapter, and vanadium, The_Ethicist and others who had a quick look and gave positive feedback.</p>
<p>During development this chapter was entitled &quot;Genocide Run&quot;, which I thought was a really powerful and alarming phrase, but the association with Undertale would just overwhelm my actual intended meaning, so there you go. Other omitted bits and bobs are</p>
<ul>
<li>rainstorms of the white maggots</li>
<li>luminous memetic hurricane anomalies</li>
<li>a bit where the Foundation's use of paper files is discussed</li>
<li>Wheeler discovering a containment unit purportedly containing an SCP which links to another reality &#8212; the unit turns out to be filled to the top with hard concrete</li>
<li>Wheeler discovering a containment unit containing a device which could destroy the Earth/Moon system, giving him the <em>genuine</em> option of actually killing himself and everybody in order to end SCP-3125's presence permanently. This would have been a fairly serious dilemma but it was confusing the story rather</li>
<li>Wheeler actually finding out from SCP-4789 who Marion actually is, and reacting to that &#8212; we've been through that loop once already, this is the more intelligent direction I think</li>
<li>Wheeler getting a shield (like the ones worn by Barsin in <em><a href="/ojai">Ojai</a></em> and O5-8 in <em><a href="/the-wild-light">Wild Light</a></em>) - this was discarded because they're known to be extremely rare, and if one was available wouldn't Marion have taken it herself during the events of <em><a href="/your-last-first-day">Your Last First Day</a></em>?</li>
<li>Yes, SCP-7381 is still in the Site 41 vault among all the dead people&#8230; it got kicked underneath the truck, and Wheeler did not notice it. It would have been somewhat inconvenient for story purposes if Wheeler had found it.</li>
</ul>
<p>I had the option of having Wheeler skip the sudden gunshot step and go straight for the orbital laser gambit. (He would have needed goggles or something to protect his eyes.) There's a fine line between &quot;running theme&quot; and &quot;running out of ideas&quot;. However, three out of five people who offered an opinion said that they liked it better this way, so here we are.</p>
<p>Oh, and I was playing a lot of <em>Metroid Prime</em> while writing this one. In my head, Wheeler's exploration of Site 41 is very much along those lines, gathering information, unlocking access to new locations by acquiring keys, constantly referring to maps&#8230; no Morph Ball though.</p>

							</div>

								
