					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=571081&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227484" alt="qntm" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=571081)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;" >qntm</a></span> <span class="odate time_1583017065 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Feb 2020 22:57</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4524499">
									

<p>That was the original concept, yes. I think it's generally understood that the Foundation &quot;universe&quot; is linked to various other realities/universes, some of which also have Foundations in. What I wanted to explore was the idea that the universe where this story takes place, where SCP-3125 is loose, has been somehow locked off from the rest of the multiverse, for their protection against the memetic threat. Also, some O5s from this universe managed to escape to a different universe before these quarantine measures were put in place. And there's a possibility that one of those O5s is trying to return to this universe (breaching quarantine), either for genuine reasons, or because that O5 is a SCP-3125 carrier and wants to spread the memetic threat to that second universe. I was working on a draft SCP entry which would be written from the perspective of this second universe's Foundation, looking at their (now-broken) link back to this universe, trying to figure out what on Earth is going on in here and what to do about it. Buuuuut the draft just wouldn't come together&#8230; so I gave up on it eventually.</p>

							</div>

								
					
