														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4524665">
									

<p>Totally missed the memo on this bad boy in chat, so I'll leave it a review on site instead.</p>
<p>Quite honestly, this is polished to the level at which I would expect from you, qntm. Some of the best prose I've encountered on this damn site. Well fuckin done, as per usual.</p>
<p>That being said, I did have a small critique to make. I wish that you'd have given us more time with Wheeler in the site. I'd have loved to see him stumble across different anomalies more specifically, just to see how he reacts to some of the things that the Foundation deals with every day. I also would have loved to follow him into the SCP-3125 containment chamber, just to track his train of thought as a person who had experienced 3125 before knowing what it is. His perspective on the beast is a unique one and I would have liked to see him cross what the Foundation knew against what he knows, as well as to have a record of what he has learned for future reference.</p>
<p>That being said, that's but a small stylistic critique of an otherwise stunning entry. +1</p>
