				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eridian-empress" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6131197); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6131197&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227484" alt="Eridian Empress" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6131197)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eridian-empress" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6131197); return false;" >Eridian Empress</a></span> <span class="odate time_1583101093 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Mar 2020 22:18</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4526055">
									

<p>After having read this chapter (and the official author post on this page), I've finally been able to put my finger on something that's been bugging me for a while. When 3125 incarnated, did it do so throughout all of reality, or just on Earth?</p>
<p>On one hand, the fact that its foreshadowing and eventual arrival were influenced purely by events in the human noosphere, and upon its arrival it took over the human noosphere (not to mention the author post suggesting that destroying Earth and destroying all traces of humanity would permanently banish 3125,) it would seem to suggest that 3125 is purely limited to Earth and humanity.</p>
<p>On the other hand, the fact that 3125 is explicitly described as extrauniversal and imposing ourself on this reality, combined with this chapter implying (or at least seeming to imply) that the sky itself has been wiped clean and that 3125's visage is all that exists of the greater cosmos would suggest that 3125 is universe-wide.</p>
<p>This wouldn't be a problem if humanity were the only sapient species in the universe. But it's a reasonable assumption to believe that intelligent extraterrestrial life exists, especially in the SCPverse. If 3125 wanted to take over the universe, you'd think that to do so it'd have to attack every noosphere in the universe. But it seems that it can succeed just from preying on a single species.</p>
<hr />
<p>None of this is to be construed as criticism, not by any means. I am absolutely in love with this chapter and the series as a whole, I just wanted to take the opportunity to ask this question that has been bothering me.</p>

							</div>

								
					
