				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=571081&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227484" alt="qntm" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=571081)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;" >qntm</a></span> <span class="odate time_1583111190 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Mar 2020 01:06</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4526272">
									

<p>I think the real question you're asking is why SCP-3125 hasn't ever shown up on Earth because it was attacking the noosphere of some other alien race which happens to think very much like humans. And&#8230; I guess there are a few possible answers to that question.</p>
<p>One possibility is: it has. But I dislike that for a whole bunch of obvious reasons.</p>
<p>Another possibility is: aliens do not <em>think</em> like we do. Even those who are most similar to humans keep their ideas in alien regions of the noosphere, distant from ours, and difficult to access. (The idea of making an expedition from the human noosphere to an alien's is a really interesting one, though!)</p>
<p>Another possibility is that sapient species create their own entire realities. The reality collectively experienced by humans is not the reality collectively experienced by the aliens. One of these realities is dominated by SCP-3125, the other is not.</p>
<p>Another is that light travel time comes into play and no alien will notice the problem for millennia. I don't really know how this affects anything&#8230;</p>
<p>The real answer to that question is that the memetics of extraterrestrials are way, way outside of the scope of the current story. The questions are answerable but the answers would be inconvenient. It would just be this immense derail from what the story is actually about.</p>
<p>At one point a few years ago I had an extremely vague idea of a third Antimemetics Division story provisionally pitched as &quot;Antimemes In Space&quot; which would address, for example, where exactly SCP-7381 came from, and what you see when you ingest Class-Z mnestics while outdoors on a clear night and look up. But I have a hundred unused ideas along those lines, and, oof, no.</p>
<p>So, to conclude, I invite you to write your own SCP or Tale addressing this point!</p>

							</div>

								
					
